# ReplyRight — sample configuration file
#
# INSTRUCTIONS
# 1. Copy this file to the ReplyRight install directory (next to ReplyRight.exe)
#    and rename it to ".env" (remove the "sample." prefix).
# 2. Fill in all REQUIRED values before launching the application.
# 3. On first launch, the app will guide you through connecting to Supabase.
#
# Alternatively, you can leave this file in place and enter credentials
# directly in the first-run setup screen that appears when you launch the app.
#
# SECURITY
# - Never share your .env file.
# - SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY and API keys must never be committed to version
#   control. Official owner-built release installers may include deployment
#   credentials provisioned from GitHub Actions secrets.
# - The anon key (SUPABASE_KEY) is safe to share only when RLS is configured.

# ── Supabase (REQUIRED for user management and feedback sync) ─────────────────
SUPABASE_URL=
SUPABASE_KEY=
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY is privileged — enter it via the first-run screen.
# If you prefer to pre-configure: fill it in here before first launch.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=

# ── AI provider (REQUIRED for AI-powered triage) ─────────────────────────────
# Anthropic Claude is the primary provider.
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
ANTHROPIC_MODEL=claude-opus-4-7

# ── Application ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
APP_HOST=127.0.0.1
APP_PORT=8000

# ── Database (leave blank to use default location) ───────────────────────────
# Default: %LOCALAPPDATA%\Programs\ReplyRight\data\hotel_email_triage.sqlite3
SQLITE_DB_PATH=
